author: Mel Buttigieg
title: Barossa Valley man dead during arrest at wine packing centre - Yahoo7
text:
Share Barossa Valley man dead during arrest at wine packing centre - Yahoo7 A man has died at a wine packing centre in South Australia's Barossa Valley during an arrest on Tuesday night. Close Man dies during arrest in Barossa Valley UP NEXT VIDEO Man dies during arrest in Barossa Valley. Source: 7 News Man dies during arrest in Barossa Valley 
Patrols were called to an area on Breakneck Hill Road, Penrice, about 10pm after reports of property damage at winemaking facility Vinpac International. A man has died at a wine packing centre in South Australia's Barossa Valley during an arrest last night. Pictures: Sunrise 
A 35-year-old Barossa Valley man was found in the Angaston area where he was arrested. 
"After the man was arrested he suffered a medical episode and subsequently died," police said in a statement. 
Police officers are at the scene investigating the incident this morning. 
More to come. Police remain at the scene Wednesday morning. Picture: Sunrise 
News break - February 8
